I have gone through the break-in period of using high brass but have yet to use any low-brass through it. Because of the modifications I'm almost certain with a tightening up of the adjustable gas plug (during use of low-brass) you can be able to go through a full 20-round drum of WallyWorld bulk pack or even worse WWB without a single problem. This is a serious killing machine with the reliability of the AK47 platform and the devastation and destruction of a 12 gauge shotgun. I have had to use it only in ONE instance against another persons (late-night robbery attempt) and the very sound of the bolt-carrier slamming home with a fresh round was enough to send the group scattering screaming "he has a gun!" This gun has been at the top of my current collection but it's time to sell it and move onto a different platform.

I am negotiable on the price but by very little. Finding a converted gun with so much extras is very difficult for such a solid price. Heck, just finding a Saiga-12 for sale in a gun shop is hard enough.
